Please join us @officialj4g â€œLondon Fashion week is a perennial event in the international calendar and highlights the world talent, creativity and inspiration in our diverse city.
The fire at Grenfell Tower is the unfashionable side of London where 72 people needlessly lost their lives. Their deaths will not be in vain. 
We are honoured to be part of LFW that will assist our campaign in keeping a global focus on what happened at Grenfell and to support the bereaved families in their continued fight for truth and justice.
The accountable authorities have been inadequate and tardy in their response and 20 months on; no significant changes or improvements have been made and no one to date has been held responsible. 
These factors and issues are fundamental to ensuring that nothing like this is ever allowed to happen again.â€ Yvette Williams J4G campaign coordinator.

This week, l travelled to Athens against medical advice for one of the most exciting shoots in my career with @marieclairegreece. The amazing team then surprised me with an award, that I was not able to accept as was rushed home for another emergency surgery. Iâ€™m not a melodramatic person and donâ€™t normally share intimate details of my life, but since so many of you have been asking, I thought Iâ€™d explain â€”especially as I can get myself into trouble for being facetious in the face of adversity. Through these testing times though, where I have had to cancel everything from a VIPâ€™s bachelorette, to every single work commitment in my diary, not to mention my dream holiday and a few weddings, I have found that laughing my way through the bad news is the only way to stay sane. It is only a (now very) dodgy foot, after all. I hope to be back to my usual antics very soon. In the meanwhile, please bear with me while I beat this thing! And for anyone else also going through hard times, sending you strength and love. We got this! â¤ï¸
